doc.title: Elekta: Q1 call highlights - We remain on the sidelines
doc.source_uri: 25.9月 普通个人版/9.1 普通个人版/JPM/JPM Elekta Q1 call highlights - We remain on the sidelinesJPM Elekta Q1 call highlights - We remain on the sidelines_2025-08-28

passages.text: Rally has faded with shares off \(c4.7\%\) at the time of writing with little from the call for the bulls. For Q2, management pointed to no revenue growth in Q2 (after \(3\%\) in Q1). Re EVO, CEO sounded a bit soft on US approval. Re China: Expected to improve in H2. In our view, this is at odds with more cautious commentary elsewhere. Re FX: CFO would not quantify the impact for the rest of the year for top line or margins. With growth H2 weighted, we remain on the sidelines.

EVO approval: CEO was a little bit soft on when EVO (new product) might be approved in the US: 'We hope for it sooner rather than later, but we don't know' and added that it is very difficult to predict a timeline for approval.
Tariff headwinds: 90bp tariff impact on margins in Q1 expected to continue going forward for the remaining quarters.
FX headwinds: CFO would not quantify the FX impact for the rest of the year on either top line or margins but expects the headwind to sequentially decline q/q.

FY outlook: Management expect a recovery of growth in China in H2 and reiterated FY group outlook for net sales in constant currency to grow y/y (consensus \(4.3\%\) ) but would not provide much colour on margin expectations for the FY.
